<HL>
   International Brief -- Mitsubishi Oil Co.:
   Merlin Petroleum Purchase
   By Firm and Unit Is Set
</HL>
<DATE>
07/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   A.BON J.MBO CHV BP
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Bond Corp. Holdings Ltd. said that a company jointly owned
by Mitsubishi Oil Co. and a Mitsubishi unit will buy Merlin
Petroleum Co. for $75 million. Bond, based in Australia, said
it holds 79.5% of Merlin. Mitsubishi is a Japanese oil
refiner and distributor.
   Merlin holds exploration interests in Papua New Guinea, in
a concession operated by Chevron Corp. British Petroleum PLC
also holds a stake in the concession. People familiar with
the transaction said production in the concession area is
expected to begin in 1992.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The sale, which is subject to regulatory and contractual
procedures, is expected to be completed before July 31.
</TEXT>
